WEBVTT

00:07.485 --> 00:10.923
Previously onYoung Sheldon...So, he's really good

00:10.967 --> 00:12.882
to graduate?He sure is.

00:12.925 --> 00:14.666
Do you think I can make it
from one end

00:14.710 --> 00:16.364
of the college campusto the other

00:16.407 --> 00:18.366
in under ten minutes,
including a bathroom break?

00:18.409 --> 00:19.845
How important
is the bathroom break?

00:19.889 --> 00:21.847
Very. The class schedules
are designed

00:21.891 --> 00:24.415
for fully grown bladders,
and mine is child-sized.

00:24.459 --> 00:25.851
One other bit of business.

00:25.895 --> 00:27.723
Since you're graduatingtop of the class,

00:27.766 --> 00:29.725
that makes you
our valedictorian.

00:29.768 --> 00:31.901
I'm so proud of you, baby.

00:31.944 --> 00:33.163
You seem surprised.

00:33.207 --> 00:35.383
Well, it's quite
an accomplishment.

00:35.426 --> 00:37.472
In this school?
I don't think so.

00:38.473 --> 00:40.344
We're really gonna miss you.

00:42.346 --> 00:45.480
ADULT SHELDON:
I've always enjoyed
math word problems.

00:45.523 --> 00:47.525
Try wrapping your noggin
around this one.

00:47.569 --> 00:50.180
A brilliant young boy
named Sheldon

00:50.224 --> 00:51.573
is about to start college.

00:51.616 --> 00:53.531
He needs to get
from his linear algebra class

00:53.575 --> 00:56.752
to his physics class,
which is 822 meters away.

00:56.795 --> 01:00.886
If his stride is 23 inches long and he only has

01:00.930 --> 01:03.933
ten minutes, how many steps would he have to take per minute

01:03.976 --> 01:06.762
to make it on time?
It's a doozy, isn't it?

01:06.805 --> 01:08.807
Don't worry.

01:08.851 --> 01:10.287
I'll show my work.

01:10.331 --> 01:13.464
First, we must determine the maximum velocity achievable

01:13.508 --> 01:15.945
without breaking a sweat.

01:15.988 --> 01:17.729
Sweating is for jocks

01:17.773 --> 01:20.863
and those who are worried
the jig is up.

01:20.906 --> 01:22.952
♪

01:27.522 --> 01:29.001
BILLY:
Hi, Sheldon.

01:29.045 --> 01:31.003
Not now, Billy. I'm in the
middle of a math problem.

01:31.047 --> 01:32.353
Okay.

01:32.396 --> 01:33.441
[chicken clucking]

01:35.747 --> 01:37.140
Darn it.

01:39.186 --> 01:40.752
MEEMAW:
What are you looking for?

01:40.796 --> 01:42.058
Chest hairs.

01:42.102 --> 01:43.799
Is there any chance
I'll hit puberty

01:43.842 --> 01:44.843
in the next few weeks?

01:44.887 --> 01:47.368
Oh, God, I hope not. Why?

01:47.411 --> 01:48.891
The campus is so big,
I'll never make it

01:48.934 --> 01:50.066
from one class to another

01:50.110 --> 01:52.286
without a solid dose
of testosterone.

01:52.329 --> 01:55.289
Maybe they'll let youleave early so you'll have time.

01:55.332 --> 01:56.464
But the end of the class is when

01:56.507 --> 01:57.726
I point out
the teacher's mistakes.

01:57.769 --> 01:59.858
Everybody loves that.

01:59.902 --> 02:01.469
I'd say run across campus,

02:01.512 --> 02:03.253
but I know how you feel
about sweating.

02:03.297 --> 02:05.821
It's the urine of the skin.

02:05.864 --> 02:07.170
Why not ride your bike?

02:07.214 --> 02:09.259
I considered that,
but I can't let my colleagues

02:09.303 --> 02:12.219
see me with training wheels.
They'll think I'm a child.

02:12.262 --> 02:13.611
Can't have that.Mm-mm.

02:16.658 --> 02:18.225
See any fuzz growing?

02:18.268 --> 02:19.791
Let me look.

02:19.835 --> 02:21.184
Hey.[laughing]

02:21.228 --> 02:23.230
[laughs]No, Meemaw! Bad Meemaw.

02:24.231 --> 02:25.754
What do you want?

02:25.797 --> 02:27.843
I was hoping you could help me
build up my leg muscles

02:27.886 --> 02:29.323
to increase my speed.

02:29.366 --> 02:31.629
If you don't want people
chasing you, be less annoying.

02:31.673 --> 02:34.023
It's so I can get
to my classes on time.

02:34.066 --> 02:36.852
Sheldon, you know
you ain't gonna work out.

02:36.895 --> 02:38.680
I will. This is important.

02:38.723 --> 02:40.508
Fine.

02:40.551 --> 02:41.857
Here. Hold these.

02:41.900 --> 02:43.815
Now, keep your back straight

02:43.859 --> 02:45.687
and bend your knees like this.

03:03.748 --> 03:05.489
Dad, you're a football coach.

03:05.533 --> 03:07.230
Do you use human growth hormone

03:07.274 --> 03:09.580
to enhance the performance
of your players?

03:09.624 --> 03:12.714
We lost our last game
63 to nine. What do you think?

03:12.757 --> 03:15.107
I think you should
look into human growth hormone.

03:15.151 --> 03:17.806
And if you do,
send some this kid's way.

03:17.849 --> 03:20.809
ADULT SHELDON: With no access
to controlled substances,

03:20.852 --> 03:22.071
I was left with only one option.

03:22.114 --> 03:23.290
Missy, will you

03:23.333 --> 03:24.769
teach me to ride a bike
tomorrow?

03:24.813 --> 03:26.467
Why not Mom?Working.

03:26.510 --> 03:27.903
Meemaw?Old.

03:27.946 --> 03:29.731
Dad?Fat.

03:29.774 --> 03:30.993
Okay.

03:32.951 --> 03:35.476
I'm such a good person.

03:35.519 --> 03:37.086
All right. You're gonna pedal.

03:37.129 --> 03:38.957
I'm gonna run behind
and hold you up.

03:39.001 --> 03:40.176
I'm nervous.

03:40.220 --> 03:41.786
Just pedal. You'll be fine.

03:41.830 --> 03:43.135
Ready?

03:43.179 --> 03:44.963
Not really.Go.

03:46.182 --> 03:47.270
SHELDON:
I'm doing it.

03:47.314 --> 03:48.837
Okay, I'm gonna let go.Don't let go.

03:48.880 --> 03:50.752
I'm letting go.Don't let go.

03:50.795 --> 03:51.927
I already let go.You let go?

03:51.970 --> 03:53.233
I let go.

03:53.276 --> 03:54.799
I'm doing it.

03:54.843 --> 03:56.801
You're doing it!I'm doing it!

03:56.845 --> 03:58.281
[chicken clucking]

04:02.329 --> 04:05.245
♪ Nobody else
is stronger than I am ♪

04:05.288 --> 04:08.073
♪ Yesterday I moved a mountain

04:08.117 --> 04:10.728
♪ I bet I could be your hero

04:10.772 --> 04:13.078
♪ I am a mighty little man

04:13.122 --> 04:17.300
♪ I am a mighty little man.♪

04:20.390 --> 04:23.132
Dad, Sheldon got hurt.How?

04:23.175 --> 04:25.003
A chicken chased him
into a mailbox.

04:25.047 --> 04:26.178
Course it did.

04:29.051 --> 04:31.314
If I knew you could run, I
would've let you teach him.

04:31.358 --> 04:32.837
[chicken clucking]What happened?

04:32.881 --> 04:34.622
Belinda got off her leash.

04:34.665 --> 04:35.623
You okay?

04:35.666 --> 04:37.668
My arm really hurts. I want Mom.

04:37.712 --> 04:40.149
You got me.
Now, let me take a look.

04:40.192 --> 04:42.107
Don't touch it.I'm not gonna hurt you.

04:42.151 --> 04:44.327
I'm sorry, but you are too big
to be delicate.

04:44.371 --> 04:45.763
I'm delicate.

04:45.807 --> 04:47.330
Just want to see
if you can bend it.

04:47.374 --> 04:49.201
I can't. It hurts too much.

04:49.245 --> 04:52.466
I'm gonna take him
to the emergency room.

04:52.509 --> 04:53.815
Come on. [grunts]

04:53.858 --> 04:55.817
You gonna be okay?Yeah.

04:57.340 --> 04:59.603
Have fun!

05:01.083 --> 05:02.693
This is bad.

05:02.737 --> 05:04.129
You're gonna be just fine.

05:04.173 --> 05:06.088
This is the arm
I write with.

05:06.131 --> 05:08.003
This is the arm I eat with.

05:08.046 --> 05:09.657
This is the arm
I do the Vulcan salute with.

05:09.700 --> 05:10.962
Ow.

05:11.006 --> 05:12.660
It's not too swollen.That's a good sign.

05:12.703 --> 05:14.009
You're not a doctor.

05:14.052 --> 05:16.228
But I see this onthe football field all the time.

05:16.272 --> 05:18.100
Football players
are meant to be hurt.

05:18.143 --> 05:19.710
I'm meant to be cherished.

05:19.754 --> 05:22.887
Okay. Looks like
you fractured your ulna.

05:22.931 --> 05:24.193
Oh, no.

05:24.236 --> 05:26.238
Two weeks in a cast,
you'll be good as new.

05:26.282 --> 05:28.371
A cast? Don't those get sweaty?Mm-hmm.

05:28.415 --> 05:29.851
They can.And itchy?

05:29.894 --> 05:31.374
A little.Can it get wet?

05:31.418 --> 05:32.506
Not supposed to.

05:32.549 --> 05:33.985
Then how am I supposed
to take a shower?

05:34.029 --> 05:35.683
Well, some people wrap it
in a garbage bag.

05:35.726 --> 05:37.380
That's where garbage goes.

05:37.424 --> 05:40.383
Did you get a discount doctor
because we're poor?

05:40.427 --> 05:42.385
Shelly, you okay?I fractured

05:42.429 --> 05:43.865
my ulna.He's fine.

05:43.908 --> 05:45.388
I told you you didn't need
to come down here.

05:45.432 --> 05:47.738
My baby is
in the emergency room.

05:47.782 --> 05:49.261
Yeah, with his father.

05:49.305 --> 05:50.698
Who let him get hurt.

05:50.741 --> 05:51.873
Me? I wasn't even there.

05:51.916 --> 05:53.222
If anything,
it was Missy's fault.

05:53.265 --> 05:54.702
And Belinda Sparks.

05:54.745 --> 05:56.268
Who?A chicken.

05:56.312 --> 05:58.096
What does a chicken
have to do with this?

05:58.140 --> 05:59.794
You know what,
I'm gonna let the nurse come in

05:59.837 --> 06:01.012
and put the cast on.

06:02.274 --> 06:04.668
Don't worry, baby. You're
gonna be just fine.

06:04.712 --> 06:07.410
Thanks, Mom.That's what I been saying
the whole time.

06:07.454 --> 06:09.804
But she cherishes me.

06:15.070 --> 06:16.376
That's so cool.

06:16.419 --> 06:17.594
Can I sign it?

06:17.638 --> 06:18.987
Why?

06:19.030 --> 06:20.728
'Cause that's what kids do.

06:20.771 --> 06:22.469
Why would I care what kids do?

06:22.512 --> 06:25.036
So when it's over,you can have a cool reminder?

06:25.080 --> 06:27.169
I don't want a reminder.
This is traumatic.

06:27.212 --> 06:29.214
I might need counseling.

06:29.258 --> 06:31.303
Come on, don't be lame.Let me sign it.

06:31.347 --> 06:33.523
You're just gonna
write something mean.

06:33.567 --> 06:35.743
You don't commit a crime
and sign your own name.

06:35.786 --> 06:36.918
Learned that onethe hard way.

06:36.961 --> 06:38.789
[doorbell rings]

06:38.833 --> 06:40.704
Oh.

06:40.748 --> 06:42.010
Hey, Brenda.

06:42.053 --> 06:44.926
Hey. I just wanted to check in

06:44.969 --> 06:47.450
and see how Sheldon's doing.

06:47.494 --> 06:50.018
He'll be fine.
It's just a little fracture.

06:50.061 --> 06:52.150
Oh. Poor kid.

06:52.194 --> 06:56.067
Please know we feel terrible.

06:56.111 --> 06:57.852
Eh, accidents happen.

06:57.895 --> 06:59.854
Hey, speaking of accidents,

06:59.897 --> 07:02.552
which this clearly was,

07:02.596 --> 07:05.250
insurance covers
everything, right?

07:05.294 --> 07:08.036
If you're worried about me
sending you a bill, don't be.

07:08.079 --> 07:09.603
Wasn't worried.

07:09.646 --> 07:12.388
I just wanted to bring you
some food as a peace offering

07:12.432 --> 07:14.956
and promise
it will never happen again.

07:14.999 --> 07:17.088
Well, thanks.

07:17.132 --> 07:19.177
Ooh, fried chicken.

07:21.223 --> 07:23.660
Never again.

07:24.618 --> 07:26.968
"I hope your armgets better soon.

07:27.011 --> 07:30.537
XO, Missy." See?

07:30.580 --> 07:33.061
Nothing mean.Thank you.

07:33.104 --> 07:34.889
ADULT SHELDON:
My sister could have
a big heart.

07:34.932 --> 07:36.717
If only that were true
of her brain.

07:36.760 --> 07:38.370
That's the wrong "your."

07:38.414 --> 07:39.415
What are you talking about?

07:39.459 --> 07:41.156
It's supposed to be Y-O-U-R.

07:41.199 --> 07:44.202
What you wrote means, "I
hope you are arm gets better."

07:44.246 --> 07:45.813
Oh.

07:45.856 --> 07:48.511
You defaced my body
with a grammatical error.

07:48.555 --> 07:51.471
I guess that's yourproblem.
Y-O-U-R.

07:55.953 --> 07:59.087
Left-handed knocking. Wild.

07:59.130 --> 08:01.611
Georgie?GEORGE JR.:
What?

08:02.656 --> 08:04.614
You're left-handed.Now that I've joined your ranks,

08:04.658 --> 08:07.530
I was wondering if you could
tell me what to expect.

08:07.574 --> 08:09.924
I don't know.
To me, it's just normal.

08:09.967 --> 08:12.230
But the vast majority of people
are right-handed.

08:12.274 --> 08:14.189
There must be some challenges.

08:15.277 --> 08:17.105
It's hard to cut stuff
with scissors.

08:17.148 --> 08:19.020
Mom handles
most of my cutting needs.

08:19.063 --> 08:21.805
Uh, when you shake hands,
it's the wrong hand.

08:21.849 --> 08:24.504
I don't shake hands.
It's disgusting.

08:25.505 --> 08:27.071
Oh! When driving,

08:27.115 --> 08:28.638
the gear shifter's
on the right side.

08:28.682 --> 08:30.597
And I'm not old enough to drive.

08:30.640 --> 08:32.163
Being a lefty
doesn't seem so bad.

08:32.207 --> 08:33.164
I don't know why

08:33.208 --> 08:34.905
you complain so much.

08:38.343 --> 08:40.476
Don't worry, baby.

08:40.520 --> 08:43.131
I cut everything into
bite-size pieces for you.

08:43.174 --> 08:45.481
Maybe you could chew it upand spit it in his mouth.

08:45.525 --> 08:48.049
Please?Let's just say grace.

08:52.183 --> 08:54.142
Will you two help him
with his mittens?

08:54.185 --> 08:55.578
Maybe he doesn't wear them.

08:55.622 --> 08:57.014
Then I'm not holding hands.

08:57.058 --> 08:58.842
We ain't gotto hold hands? Sweet.

08:58.886 --> 09:01.279
I like when we hold hands.We are holding hands.

09:01.323 --> 09:02.629
Let's go. Mittens.

09:02.672 --> 09:04.152
Fine.Fine.

09:04.195 --> 09:06.154
Gently. Gently.

09:06.197 --> 09:07.503
I'm doing it gently.

09:07.547 --> 09:09.200
Well, your tone
suggests otherwise.

09:09.244 --> 09:10.637
Just give me your hand.

09:12.160 --> 09:13.553
Gently.

09:14.815 --> 09:17.034
[sighs]
There.

09:18.645 --> 09:21.735
Bless us, Lord, for the foodwe are about to receive,

09:21.778 --> 09:23.214
and bless the handsthat prepared it.

09:23.258 --> 09:26.435
And bless Sheldon's arm
to heal strong and quick.

09:26.478 --> 09:27.610
Strongly and quickly.

09:27.654 --> 09:28.872
Amen.

09:28.916 --> 09:30.831
ALL:
Amen.

09:30.874 --> 09:33.224
I've never operated a fork
with my left hand before.

09:33.268 --> 09:34.530
I hope this goes well.

09:34.574 --> 09:36.880
When my buddy Mikey got the castoff his leg,

09:36.924 --> 09:39.796
you would not believehow skinny and smelly it was.

09:39.840 --> 09:42.016
Like beef jerky with toes.

09:42.059 --> 09:43.365
Can we please just eat?

09:46.237 --> 09:47.195
Chicken's good.

09:47.238 --> 09:48.849
Mrs. Sparks made it.

09:48.892 --> 09:50.067
Huh?

09:53.680 --> 09:55.203
My first
bathroom attempt.

09:55.246 --> 09:57.205
Let's hope
this goes well.

09:57.248 --> 10:00.208
Let me know if you need help.

10:00.251 --> 10:01.383
I think I'll be okay.

10:01.426 --> 10:03.254
It's just number one.

10:03.298 --> 10:04.778
I'm here if you need me.

10:07.607 --> 10:10.218
Mom, I can't get
my zipper down!

10:10.261 --> 10:13.003
I'm coming.

10:13.047 --> 10:14.526
ADULT SHELDON:
I am not saying

10:14.570 --> 10:17.660
my mother and I had
a codependent relationship.

10:17.704 --> 10:20.881
Mom, I can't get
my zipper up!

10:20.924 --> 10:22.230
I'm on my way!

10:22.273 --> 10:23.579
ADULT SHELDON:
But she did have a tendency

10:23.623 --> 10:25.233
to baby me, and boy howdy,

10:25.276 --> 10:26.669
was I okay with that.

10:26.713 --> 10:28.758
♪ Well, I don't know
if all that's true... ♪

10:28.802 --> 10:32.022
How's this?It's like I'm doing it myself.

10:32.066 --> 10:33.502
♪ And, baby, I got you

10:33.545 --> 10:35.460
Mm.

10:35.504 --> 10:36.984
♪ Babe...

10:37.027 --> 10:39.247
SHELDON:
Mm-mm.

10:39.290 --> 10:40.727
Ooh, you got it.

10:40.770 --> 10:42.729
MARY: Yup, chicken.♪ I got you, babe...

10:42.772 --> 10:45.819
I don't haveto tell you to be gentle.

10:45.862 --> 10:47.908
No, you don't.

10:47.951 --> 10:50.171
[shower running]

10:50.214 --> 10:52.826
Washcloth?Washcloth.

10:52.869 --> 10:54.088
Soap?

10:54.131 --> 10:56.046
Soap.

10:56.090 --> 10:57.265
Shampoo?

10:57.308 --> 10:59.006
Shampoo.

10:59.049 --> 11:00.355
SHELDON:
Baby shampoo?

11:00.398 --> 11:02.357
Does E equal MC squared?

11:02.400 --> 11:03.575
Love you.

11:03.619 --> 11:05.099
♪ I got you to understand...

11:05.142 --> 11:07.536
"The quantum properties
of matter are to be associated

11:07.579 --> 11:11.583
"with incompletely
defined potentialities,

11:11.627 --> 11:14.282
which can be more
definitely realized..."

11:14.325 --> 11:16.676
♪ I got you, babe.

11:19.548 --> 11:21.115
All right,
you're gonna pedal.

11:21.158 --> 11:23.334
I'm gonna run behind
and hold you up.

11:23.378 --> 11:24.466
I'm nervous.

11:24.509 --> 11:25.946
Just pedal. You'll be fine.

11:25.989 --> 11:27.599
MARY'S VOICE:
You're gonna get hurt!

11:27.643 --> 11:28.992
What?

11:29.036 --> 11:30.646
Put us back on!

11:30.690 --> 11:31.821
Mom?

11:31.865 --> 11:34.084
You need us.
We'll keep you safe!

11:34.128 --> 11:36.304
This is weird.

11:36.347 --> 11:37.653
We're a team.

11:37.697 --> 11:40.308
You and I belong together.

11:40.351 --> 11:42.919
No. I have to grow up
and go to college.

11:42.963 --> 11:44.355
Forever!

11:44.399 --> 11:45.617
Getting weirder.

11:45.661 --> 11:47.315
Forever...

11:47.358 --> 11:49.447
and ever!

11:53.669 --> 11:55.279
MARY'S VOICE:
Forever and ever and ever.

11:55.323 --> 11:59.631
"That is, if we try to
picture the position..."No.

11:59.675 --> 12:01.808
Mom's my training wheels.

12:01.851 --> 12:04.811
I can't have training wheels.

12:04.854 --> 12:08.684
Mom's my training wheels.Lot of noise over there.

12:08.728 --> 12:10.773
[TV playing indistinctly]

12:10.817 --> 12:12.253
Everything okay?

12:12.296 --> 12:13.254
I'm not sure.

12:13.297 --> 12:14.516
What's going on?

12:14.559 --> 12:17.911
Ugh. He was muttering
in his sleep that

12:17.954 --> 12:19.434
I am his training wheels.

12:19.477 --> 12:21.915
What on earth does that mean?

12:21.958 --> 12:23.612
Well, let's think about it.

12:23.655 --> 12:25.266
Training wheels arefor little kids.

12:25.309 --> 12:28.312
Maybe he doesn't wantto be a little kid anymore.

12:28.356 --> 12:30.488
What does that have
to do with me?

12:30.532 --> 12:32.012
[laughs]

12:32.055 --> 12:35.102
You have made it your life'smission to hold him up.

12:35.145 --> 12:36.930
What are you saying here?

12:36.973 --> 12:39.367
That I am wrong to love
and protect my son?

12:39.410 --> 12:42.413
That he doesn't need his
mother to keep an eye on him?

12:42.457 --> 12:43.937
I'm not saying that. I...

12:43.980 --> 12:45.590
I would never say that.

12:45.634 --> 12:48.028
All right then.

12:49.943 --> 12:52.075
I'm not an idiot.

12:53.511 --> 12:55.122
MARY:
Did you have

12:55.165 --> 12:57.864
a tough time when your kidsstarted being independent?

12:57.907 --> 12:58.995
I'll let you know.

12:59.039 --> 13:00.780
What does that mean?

13:00.823 --> 13:02.869
Means one of 'em is still
sitting in my kitchen

13:02.912 --> 13:04.566
whining about something.

13:04.609 --> 13:08.265
Could you be supportivefor once?

13:09.440 --> 13:12.704
Yes, watching your kids
grow up is hard.

13:12.748 --> 13:14.489
So how do you handle it?

13:14.532 --> 13:17.231
I find a little bourbon
in my coffee does the trick.

13:17.274 --> 13:19.450
And we're backto being not helpful.

13:21.017 --> 13:23.106
Look, you haven't even gotten
to the worst part of it yet.

13:23.150 --> 13:24.499
They're gonna leave home.

13:24.542 --> 13:27.328
They're gonna move
to another city.Oh, Lord.

13:27.371 --> 13:28.633
They're gonna tell you

13:28.677 --> 13:31.419
their loser boyfriend
has knocked them up.

13:31.462 --> 13:34.726
Just to be clear,
that would be you.Sorry.

13:34.770 --> 13:37.860
Turned my hair
gray overnight.I said sorry.

13:37.904 --> 13:40.080
Clearly, you're notin the mood to help.

13:40.123 --> 13:43.735
Listen, it's hard
being a parent,

13:43.779 --> 13:48.218
but if you do it right,
they don't need you anymore.

13:48.262 --> 13:50.133
Well, I don't like that.

13:50.177 --> 13:53.702
I get it, but I justdon't like it.

13:53.745 --> 13:57.793
Well, I'd point out, you'll
always have your husband,

13:57.837 --> 14:00.927
but you want me to be "helpful."

14:03.320 --> 14:06.976
Johannes Diderik van der Waals.

14:07.020 --> 14:09.936
Nils Gustaf Dalén.

14:09.979 --> 14:11.938
Heike Kamerlingh Onnes.

14:11.981 --> 14:13.504
What are you going?

14:13.548 --> 14:16.290
Listing Nobel Prize winners
in physics.

14:16.333 --> 14:17.639
Why?

14:17.682 --> 14:19.771
To keep me from cracking
this cast like a coconut

14:19.815 --> 14:21.904
and scratching my skin off.

14:21.948 --> 14:23.645
I need Mom
to sing "Soft Kitty."

14:23.688 --> 14:25.299
Don't do it.

14:25.342 --> 14:26.648
Why?

14:26.691 --> 14:28.171
You're being a baby again.

14:28.215 --> 14:29.390
But I'm injured.

14:29.433 --> 14:31.740
Big deal. You broke your arm.

14:31.783 --> 14:33.916
Look at Stephen
Hawking over there.

14:33.960 --> 14:35.962
He's in a wheelchair.

14:36.005 --> 14:38.747
You don't hear him whining
about it with his robot voice.

14:41.010 --> 14:43.491
So you're saying
he and I are brilliant minds

14:43.534 --> 14:47.016
who have both suffered
great physical adversity.

14:47.060 --> 14:48.975
That's not even close
to what I'm saying.

14:49.018 --> 14:50.411
Well, that's what I heard.

14:50.454 --> 14:51.978
And if Hawking

14:52.021 --> 14:53.457
doesn't let it stop him,

14:53.501 --> 14:55.720
then I can't
let this cast stop me.

14:55.764 --> 14:57.157
Great. Go back to sleep.

14:57.200 --> 15:00.421
I will, and I'll do it
all by myself.

15:06.906 --> 15:09.169
♪ Soft kitty, warm kitty

15:09.212 --> 15:13.216
Oh, my God.♪ Little ball of fur

15:13.260 --> 15:16.437
♪ Happy kitty,
sleepy kitty, purr ♪

15:16.480 --> 15:18.961
♪ Purr, purr.

15:26.969 --> 15:28.884
I did it.

15:28.928 --> 15:30.190
Missy, I did it!

15:30.233 --> 15:32.888
[groans]
What?

15:32.932 --> 15:34.890
I slept through the night.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.065
What time is it?

15:36.109 --> 15:37.980
6:14.

15:38.024 --> 15:40.852
This is why people hate you.

15:40.896 --> 15:44.204
ADULT SHELDON:
My sister's crankiness
did not dampen my enthusiasm.

15:44.247 --> 15:46.989
A chicken may have
fractured my arm,

15:47.033 --> 15:49.470
but nothing could break
my can-do spirit.

15:49.513 --> 15:52.342
All in the bowl, none on me.

15:52.386 --> 15:54.170
I call that
a successful urination.

15:54.214 --> 15:56.259
Great.
Go teach your brother.

15:56.303 --> 15:58.479
♪ There's no stopping me...

15:58.522 --> 16:02.570
I will not be denied my jelly.[lid pops]

16:02.613 --> 16:03.832
Yes!

16:03.875 --> 16:07.183
Watch out, peanut butter.
You're next.

16:07.227 --> 16:08.532
Who would like to tell us

16:08.576 --> 16:10.665
how God touched their lives
this week?

16:10.708 --> 16:12.232
Sheldon.

16:12.275 --> 16:14.408
He didn't,
because He doesn't exist.

16:14.451 --> 16:15.931
Then why raise your hand?

16:15.975 --> 16:17.715
Not just any hand.
My left hand.

16:17.759 --> 16:20.196
Because I'm able
to overcome any obstacle.

16:20.240 --> 16:21.981
And maybe
God helped you do that.

16:22.024 --> 16:23.591
Actually,
it was Stephen Hawking,

16:23.634 --> 16:25.419
and he's better
because he exists.

16:25.462 --> 16:27.987
Yes, 'cause God made him.Anybody else?

16:28.030 --> 16:30.728
Billy.Is this gonna be on the test?

16:30.772 --> 16:31.773
Oh, boy.

16:31.816 --> 16:33.166
ADULT SHELDON:
I took a moment

16:33.209 --> 16:36.082
to reflect on my journey
of the last two weeks.

16:36.125 --> 16:41.565
Such emotional growth was worthy of a majestic bubble beard.

16:41.609 --> 16:43.306
♪ Don't stop me,have a good time, good time... ♪

16:43.350 --> 16:46.788
ADULT SHELDON:
Perhaps my sister was right.

16:46.831 --> 16:50.139
This was a time
I'd want to remember.

16:50.183 --> 16:52.315
Dad, will you sign my cast?

16:52.359 --> 16:54.404
Sure.

16:57.538 --> 17:00.845
And if you have any grammar
questions, please ask first.

17:00.889 --> 17:02.804
[sighs]

17:05.415 --> 17:08.549
"Have a great summer. Georgie."

17:09.680 --> 17:11.421
Normally I'd write,"Have a bitchin' summer,"

17:11.465 --> 17:12.901
but I figuredyou wouldn't like that.

17:12.944 --> 17:14.076
I wouldn't.

17:14.120 --> 17:15.904
ADULT SHELDON:
My meemaw wrote...

17:15.947 --> 17:17.906
"To my brave Moon Pie.

17:17.949 --> 17:22.084
You handled this
like a true Texan."

17:22.128 --> 17:23.303
[laughs]

17:23.346 --> 17:24.826
ADULT SHELDON:
My mom wrote...

17:24.869 --> 17:27.785
MARY:
"Shelly, you'll always
be my baby,

17:27.829 --> 17:31.485
"but I'm so proud of the young man you've become.

17:31.528 --> 17:33.661
Love, Mom."

17:34.879 --> 17:36.490
ADULT SHELDON:
And Billy wrote...

17:36.533 --> 17:38.057
BILLY:
"Billy."

17:44.237 --> 17:46.065
ADULT SHELDON: The next day,
I got my cast off.

17:46.108 --> 17:49.285
In a world where I valued
symmetry, I was relieved

17:49.329 --> 17:54.856
to see that both my arms were as pale and skinny as ever.

17:54.899 --> 17:58.381
But this Texan had unfinished
business to tend to.

17:58.425 --> 17:59.861
Want me to get
you started?

17:59.904 --> 18:02.211
No, I can do it.

18:06.346 --> 18:08.565
ADULT SHELDON:
And I did do it.

18:08.609 --> 18:12.134
I rode my bike without
training wheels like an adult.

18:12.178 --> 18:13.483
It would take more
than a chicken

18:13.527 --> 18:15.790
or the threat of a fractured bone to scare me.

18:15.833 --> 18:18.532
It would take a brown beast
named Scraps.

18:18.575 --> 18:20.969
[barking]Aah!

18:21.012 --> 18:22.579
Mommy?!

18:22.623 --> 18:24.929
ADULT SHELDON:
I rode my bike 11 miles
that day.

18:24.973 --> 18:26.409
Mommy!

